                            <comment id="445126" author="bobijam" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2025 09:33:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;w/o this patch, the &quot;mirror split -d&quot; would get -EINVAL from LOD, and print something &quot;cannot get UNLOCK lease, ext 8&quot;, and lfs would fall back to old mirror split method and succeed it. So eventually the mirror split would succeed, but would print this annoying error message on screen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="445108" author="bzzz" created="Thu, 20 Feb 2025 04:59:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;do you remember what exact error we get w/o this patch? is it returned via close() ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436916" author="bobijam" created="Thu, 28 Nov 2024 18:07:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I thought I pushed it but I didn&apos;t, I&apos;m pushing it now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436277" author="bzzz" created="Sat, 23 Nov 2024 04:30:29 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The updated patch has removed lod_check_layout_gen_intrans/lod_save_layout_gen_intrans&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;can&apos;t find this, can you point out, please?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436174" author="bobijam" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2024 12:04:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alex,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The updated patch has removed lod_check_layout_gen_intrans/lod_save_layout_gen_intrans&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436063" author="bobijam" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2024 15:21:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &quot;lfs mirror split -d&quot; reports a strange &quot;cannot get UNLOCK lease&quot; but it did successfully deleted the mirror, when I try to find out where the message come from, I found this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436010" author="adilger" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2024 07:36:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bobijam&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bobijam&quot;&gt;bobijam&lt;/a&gt;, how did you find this bug?  Was it in a regression test, or should it be linked to some other ticket?  The description is very short, and doesn&apos;t tell me whether it is important, or just a trivial cleanup that you are doing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
